observations.recommendation:
We advised that the GFPS adhere to their mandates: 

Provide technical assistance and monitor the implementation of the GPB to ensure its completion and address possible solution of issues concern;
Guarantee/ensure the timely preparation and submission of GAD Accomplishment Reports (AP), and GAD Consolidation Reports regarding status of implementation of GPB;
Create GAD Monitoring and Evaluating Team which shall evaluate the outcomes of the LGU GAD policies, programs and projects;
Monitor the utilization of GAD funds as against GAD PPAs approved in the GPB notice of any overspending or under spending to avoid suspensions or disallowances of transactions. 
Strict compliance with PCW-DILG-DBM-NEDA Joint Memorandum Circular No.2016-01 dated January 12, 2016.

We advised that the Municipal Mayor require the:

Accounting Office to prepare and maintain road networks property cards and to submit Report on Local Road Network;
Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant and Municipal Treasurer with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects;
Inventory Committee to conduct inventory count of all the Municipality’s road network systems and accordingly submit a Report on the Physical Count of the Road Network System as of the end of the year; and
Municipal Accountant to prepare and maintain the prescribed property ledger cards for Local Road Networks and disclose the information for the said property in the Notes to Financial Statements in accordance with the provision cited under COA Circular No. 2015-008 dated November 23, 2015.

We recommended that the Management:
Reconcile the noted differences and require the GSO/Property Officer to document all unaccounted properties and reconcile their records with accounting records.               
Prepare the necessary complete Report on the Physical Count of PPE to establish existence and validity. 
Maintain Property Ledger Card/Property Cards update adequate accounting and property records and conduct periodic reconciliation between accounting and property records;
Exert efforts to locate all properties and records and conduct a thorough physical check and inventory of all properties. All unserviceable properties should be properly reported to serve as basis for dropping in the books of accounts by the Accounting Department;
Ensure strict adherence to the applicable laws, rules and regulations on PPE to prevent the incurrence of the deficiencies noted.

