We advised Management the following measures:

1.	Require all accountable officers to immediately submit liquidation documents for cash advances granted in prior years amounting to ₱455,215.89, as of December 31,2018, in compliance with Sections 89 and 102 of Presidential Decree No. 1445, and 97-002 dated February 5 and 10,1997;

2.	An official/employee who is separated from the service caused by reassignment/transfer/retirement/death, should not be given clearance unless their outstanding cash advances are first settled;

3.	Send out demand letter to those with unliquidated cash advances but were already separated from service;

4.	A request to the Commission Audit for write-off and/or adjustment for dormant or non-moving account as prescribed in COA Circular Nos. 2016-005. The request should be duly supported by the documents required in the said Circular.

