We advised that management:

a) require the Municipal Engineer and MPDO to provide and to take full responsibility of the preparation of the required reports and strictly observe the timely submission of the same to the Audit Team;

b) advice concerned officials to religiously adopt and comply with the full disclosure policy of the state on matters of public interest as clearly professed and embodied in the Constitution;

c) direct the Municipal Engineer to strictly comply with the required posting of information and publicity on programs/projects/activities of government agencies and inform the Audit Team within 10 days after the award of the projects or before the start of the programs/projects/activities that the appropriate project signboards and/or public notices are already posted at the project sites; and

d) refrain from incurring expenses in violation of the afore-cited Circular as this shall be disallowed in audit and subject to administrative disciplinary action provided under penalty clause of the same COA Circular.

